WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:27.869 --> 00:00:34.440
 The competitive environment is satisfied with the forces that determine profitability and allows 

00:00:34.440 --> 00:00:41.320
 a company to be more successful in the sector that wants to venture, all this is achieved 

00:00:41.320 --> 00:00:44.780
 with the five forces of Porter. 

00:00:45.829 --> 00:00:51.550
 Each force affects profitability through its impact on prices, operating costs 

00:00:51.550 --> 00:00:52.269
 and investment. 

00:00:54.900 --> 00:01:01.340
 At the potential entry of a company that accesses a sector for the first time and that 

00:01:01.440 --> 00:01:08.060
 can face existing barriers to entry and the reaction of other competitors, is 

00:01:08.060 --> 00:01:11.840
 known as Entry Threat. 

00:01:12.840 --> 00:01:18.800
 The companies that enter the market increase the productive capacity of the sector. 

00:01:27.740 --> 00:01:33.550
 The bargaining power of buyers is the potential with which customers can 

00:01:33.550 --> 00:01:38.970
 negotiate with the companies that produce a good or service. 

00:01:38.970 --> 00:01:43.910
 Strategies can be implemented to gain customer loyalty. 

00:01:49.289 --> 00:01:54.649
 The bargaining power of suppliers is the threat imposed by the power of which 

00:01:54.649 --> 00:02:00.190
 have in the cost, quality or specificity in the supply of supplies 

00:02:00.190 --> 00:02:01.810
 to the companies. 

00:02:02.400 --> 00:02:07.540
 The lower the number of suppliers, the greater their bargaining power. 

00:02:14.920 --> 00:02:20.660
 Companies that sell similar or alternative products and become threatening 

00:02:20.680 --> 00:02:27.680
 when they have a lower price they represent the Threat of substitute products. 

00:02:37.680 --> 00:02:44.019
 Rivalry among competitors takes place when companies compete to have 

00:02:44.019 --> 00:02:51.019
 a privileged place in the sector to offer the same product. 

00:02:52.890 --> 00:02:59.849
 The model of the five forces is useful to determine the degree of competition of the company, 

00:02:59.849 --> 00:03:05.760
 threats and opportunities in the market and develop strategies to overcome them. 

00:03:10.840 --> 00:03:12.060
 Threat of entry. 

00:03:12.989 --> 00:03:15.169
 Buying power of the buyers. 

00:03:16.080 --> 00:03:18.180
 Bargaining power of suppliers. 

00:03:18.640 --> 00:03:20.661
 Threat of substitute products. 

00:03:21.120 --> 00:03:23.000
 Rivalry among competitors. 

